<A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ualuaeia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aluaeia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/02 10:23:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4648.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bane Weapon Quest (Shissar and Seru)</span><hr size=1> I'm in the process of stockpiling Yttrium ore (we do know that one of the components is Yttrium) in an attempt to figure out the recipes.<br><br>According to someone who apparently does know the recipe at<br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornersmithing.showMessage?topicID=4987.topic">pub13.ezboard.com/feqtrad...4987.topic</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br><br>&quot;What *is* semi public knowledge is the following:<br>1: The weapons are no-drop<br>2: The ONLY mob in the game where the bane is applied is Lord Seru himself<br>3: They are reported non-trivial at 252 skill (not confirmed)<br>4: The componants are very rare drops from generic un-named mobs<br>5: If you ever get to a position where you're able to use the swords, you will also have the recipie&quot;<br><br>I've been told that Enlightened Dark on Tarew Marr knows the recipe, and the poster in the above quote is on Zebuxoruk (last known to be in Dark Horizon).<br><br>My guess would be that the recipe's are given to you at some point in the 4th or 5th earring of veracity quests, the one that requires Seru's head to get the next one.  I can't confirm this because I have yet to farm the Consilium reports for myself.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uhyarth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hyarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/02 12:21:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4648.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bane Weapon Quest (Shissar and Seru)</span><hr size=1> I've got to say this, because its driving me nuts.  Its a small request to everybody.  In however you want to approach this, please stop confusing Seru and Ssra.  Yes, they're both four letters.  Yes, they both share 's' and 'r' in the same locations.  But, again and again and again I see people confusing the two. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvaclavromanov.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vaclav Romanov</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/02 12:37:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4648.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bane Weapon Quest (Shissar and Seru)</span><hr size=1> Next thing you're gonna say Sanctus Seru and Ssraeshza Temple are too different zones, Hyth =P<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/untingearreaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ntin Gearreaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/7/02 11:16:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4648.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td>